# FortiGate Configuration File
# 
# Format: IP_ADDRESS, API_KEY, NAME (optional)
# Lines starting with # are ignored
#
# To use this file:
# 1. Copy this file to fortigate_config.txt
# 2. Replace the example values with your FortiGate details
# 3. Run the script and select option 2 (Load from config file)
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY WARNING: Keep this file secure - it contains API tokens!
# Add fortigate_config.txt to .gitignore to prevent accidental commits.

# Example single FortiGate:
# 192.168.1.100, fmtXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX, HQ-FortiGate

# Example A/A HA Cluster:
# 192.168.1.100, fmtXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX, FW-Primary
# 192.168.1.101, fmtYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYYY, FW-Secondary

# Example multi-site deployment:
# 10.10.1.1, fmtAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA, Site-A-Primary
# 10.10.1.2, fmtBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBBB, Site-A-Secondary
# 10.20.1.1, fmtCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCCC, Site-B-Primary
# 10.20.1.2, fmtDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDD, Site-B-Secondary